meaning_str.bing:
adj. 忙碌的；无暇的；忙于（做某事）；人来车往的
n. 包打听
v. 忙着做某事
网络. 忙的；繁忙的；占线

忙碌的；无暇的；忙于（做某事）；人来车往的

忙碌的；繁忙的；占线的（指电话）；正被占用的；热闹的；熙熙攘攘的

sogou-kaoyan.adj/v: 忙碌的; 忙于[出现6次)]

sogou-CET4.adj: 热闹的; 熙攘的[出现1次)]

sogou-zhongkao.adj: 热闹的; 熙攘的[出现14次)]

1.en: Docked at the front of the house windows of a man, she saw the men are hard working, calculate data, create charts and is too busy.
1.cn: 停靠在男人房前的窗户上，她看见男人正在辛勤地工作，计算数据，制作图表，忙得不亦乐乎。

2.en: Sure, he kills a bunch of kids, but I never wanted to get busy with a Jedi until I saw him with his shirt off.
2.cn: 淡然，他杀了大批的孩子，在他脱掉上衣之前，我从未想过会对绝地武士痴迷。

3.en: At the hotel he found Joe, too busy all day with the laundry to have come to him earlier.
3.cn: 他在旅馆发现了乔，乔成天忙于洗衣店事务，设工夭早来。

0.en: You know, I mean, God did take time out of his busy schedule to bless these Sloppy Joes. Come on, Shelly, tell me your news.
0.cn: 毕竟主可是从他忙碌的日程里抽空祝福了这些邋遢乔汉堡呢。说啊，谢利，发生什么事了。

1.en: So I'm going to use variations of dishes that my grandmother loved to cook for me to show a couple of busy mums two recipes that are quick and healthy.
1.cn: 所以我打算改良几道我奶奶爱为我做的菜，来给一些忙碌的妈妈们展示两款快速又健康的食谱。

2.en: Like most Beijingers, Zhang Yan leads a busy, modern life. But each spring, she and her family take a break to indulge in the traditions that make this time of year so special.
2.cn: 像大多数北京人，张岩过着忙碌的现代生活。但每年春季，她和她的家人会稍作休息沉湎在传统之中，令这段日子与别不同。

4.en: Hey, dad? I'm kinda busy. What's up?

5.en: You were so busy trying to be her, Riley.
5.cn: 你一心想着要变成她的样子，莱丽。

6.en: I can't leave now, Sheldon. I'm very busy.

7.cn: 找点事做，但不要耗费过多精力。

8.en: What? I'm busy. It's Malky, man. He's dead.
8.cn: 怎么了？我现在很忙。是马尔奇，他死了。

9.en: You're a busy man. I don't know the opposite.
9.cn: 你是个大忙人。我从来没闲下来过。

10.en: I guess I was just busy keeping them all alive.
10.cn: 我总是忙于让他们都活下去 所以忘记了。

11.en: Oh, gee, I don't know. My schedule's a little busy.
11.cn: 我可不知道有没有时间，我的日程有点满。

12.en: You've been busy. And you've been a complete idiot.

13.en: Because I'm too busy answering everybody's private requests for advice.
13.cn: 因为我正回复每个人的私信，给他们提建议，没空烦恼。

14.en: You have been busy, haven't you? Quite the busy little bee.
14.cn: 你一直还挺忙吧? 像小蜜蜂团团转。

15.en: Busy, isn't it? Busy? No. This is quiet for the Potato City. Have a lovely day.
15.cn: 挺热闹的，是吧？热闹吗？没有啊，今天的土豆城市已经算冷清的了。祝你们玩的愉快！

16.en: What busy bees. Yes, we're busy bees. Buzz. Now, we must fly back to our hive to make honey.
16.cn: 好勤劳的蜜蜂啊。是的，我们是勤劳的小蜜蜂，我们现在要回到蜂箱去了，去酿蜂蜜。

17.en: Why are you calling me Mr. Grady? Owen. If you're not too busy. I'm pretty busy. We have an attraction.
17.cn: 你为什么叫我格雷迪先生？欧文，如果你不是很忙的话。我忙得很。我们遇到了一个问题[互相吸引]。

18.en: But now my dad's busy with his new wife, who was his old boss. And my mom, well, she's busy not getting over that.
18.cn: 我爸爸现在和新妻子生活。爸爸的新妻子是他以前的老板。我妈妈忙着借酒消愁。

19.en: Goodness me. What do we have here? Granny. We're busy bees. Buzz. Ah. Would you busy bees like some toast? Yes, please.
19.cn: 噢天啊，这是怎么回事呀？奶奶，我们是勤劳的蜜蜂。勤劳的蜜蜂们想来吃面包吗？是的。
